being broadcast on the dark web internationally.

00:48:28.915 --> 00:48:31.915
There's a betting ring on you. These people are completely insane.

00:48:55.245 --> 00:48:57.575
Look at his defense.

00:49:08.325 --> 00:49:11.395
Go Eun, can you find the broadcasting room?

00:49:11.555 --> 00:49:15.795
- The broadcasting room? - Cheon Gwang Jin rang the bell.

00:49:16.065 --> 00:49:17.265
Showing you the way now.

00:49:29.575 --> 00:49:31.015
He's an entertaining one.

00:49:32.475 --> 00:49:34.045
- Patch into the hallway feed. - Yes, sir.

00:49:40.825 --> 00:49:41.825
The broadcasting room...

00:49:41.826 --> 00:49:43.455
is the last room on the floor directly above you.

00:49:48.895 --> 00:49:51.595
What? Why did it turn off? Next hallway.

00:49:57.575 --> 00:50:00.245
Darn it, can't you do a job properly, you jerk?

00:50:00.305 --> 00:50:01.705
It wasn't me.

00:50:01.845 --> 00:50:04.115
- I think someone else has control. - What?

00:50:04.145 --> 00:50:05.215
Directional controls aren't responding.

00:50:05.675 --> 00:50:07.515
Of course they're not.

00:50:09.115 --> 00:50:10.215
Darn it.

00:50:12.755 --> 00:50:15.124
- Got you! - Hey, people are leaving!

00:50:15.125 --> 00:50:16.955
Darn it. My money!

00:50:17.025 --> 00:50:18.055
The feed's down again.

00:50:18.295 --> 00:50:19.355
Darn it!

00:50:22.465 --> 00:50:23.895
Can't see a thing, can you?

00:50:25.995 --> 00:50:28.565
This is an interesting situation, isn't it?

00:50:31.475 --> 00:50:34.645
Why isn't this working? Get it back online, now!

00:50:34.905 --> 00:50:36.205
You're asking why?

00:50:36.845 --> 00:50:37.975
Darn it.

00:50:42.115 --> 00:50:43.615
Hey, what are you waiting for?

00:50:43.955 --> 00:50:45.085
Go check it out now!

00:50:58.495 --> 00:51:00.035
Round Three.

00:51:00.965 --> 00:51:02.035
Fight!

00:51:23.295 --> 00:51:25.695
You're surprisingly good at this.

00:51:26.925 --> 00:51:29.125
How would you like to make some real money with me?

00:51:43.575 --> 00:51:46.915
They must think anyone who shows up on screen is a player.

00:51:47.545 --> 00:51:49.645
It looks like everyone's hoping you die.

00:51:51.055 --> 00:51:54.155
- I guess that's where the money is. - It is for me.

00:51:55.985 --> 00:51:57.725
Because you're the one who's going to die here.

00:51:59.495 --> 00:52:01.795
There are some killer bets placed against you.

00:52:18.375 --> 00:52:20.245
(Jingwang Boys' Middle School)

00:52:21.645 --> 00:52:24.115
(Disciplinary spanking)

00:52:24.455 --> 00:52:26.155
I can't believe they still have these in schools.

00:52:31.325 --> 00:52:32.395
Disciplinary spanking.

00:52:43.035 --> 00:52:44.035
Does it hurt?

00:52:46.435 --> 00:52:48.045
You should have...

00:52:50.675 --> 00:52:52.015
listened to your teacher.

00:53:05.825 --> 00:53:06.825
Goodness.

00:53:07.165 --> 00:53:08.925
So you beat all the minions and made it to the final boss.

00:53:35.085 --> 00:53:36.355
You're too slow.

00:54:20.265 --> 00:54:21.365
So are you.

00:54:36.045 --> 00:54:37.685
I guess that's the one thing we have in common.

00:55:18.395 --> 00:55:20.565
You're here for Park Min Ho's body, right?

00:55:21.925 --> 00:55:23.635
I'll tell you where it is.

00:55:24.865 --> 00:55:26.465
Thanks, but I'll pass.

00:55:27.135 --> 00:55:28.335
Because I've already found him.

00:55:40.445 --> 00:55:42.115
Park Min Ho has been safely recovered.

00:55:45.715 --> 00:55:48.585
Hey, how much did that old man pay you?

00:55:50.655 --> 00:55:51.795
I'll give you...

00:55:53.055 --> 00:55:55.465
ten times that amount. Okay?

00:56:00.035 --> 00:56:01.135
No?

00:56:02.165 --> 00:56:03.335
How about 20 times?

00:56:06.505 --> 00:56:07.845
I'll pass on that too.

00:56:09.045 --> 00:56:11.175
Then just die.

00:56:27.265 --> 00:56:29.465
I just eyeballed it, but luckily, it's a perfect fit.

00:56:36.035 --> 00:56:37.135
Oh, gosh.

00:56:38.505 --> 00:56:39.905
It hurts.

00:56:41.045 --> 00:56:43.345
I think everything's broken.

00:56:46.845 --> 00:56:47.845
You know what?

00:56:48.485 --> 00:56:50.415
They say falling from three stories up...

00:56:50.985 --> 00:56:54.385
is like getting hit by a car going 60km per hour.

00:56:57.155 --> 00:56:58.325
It hurts.

00:57:01.225 --> 00:57:03.635
I need to go to a hospital.

00:57:05.535 --> 00:57:07.565
That's how Park Min Ho must've felt when you hit him with your car.

00:57:08.635 --> 00:57:10.675
And his father, Park Dong Su, must have too.

00:57:15.275 --> 00:57:16.575
What did you do back then?

00:57:19.275 --> 00:57:20.645
Did you just stand there and watch?

00:57:25.185 --> 00:57:26.455
Smiling just like this?

00:57:32.495 --> 00:57:33.695
Please spare me.

00:57:37.435 --> 00:57:39.365
Please spare me.

00:57:40.265 --> 00:57:43.005
I'll never do it again.

00:57:46.175 --> 00:57:48.575
Why? Are you scared?

00:57:49.605 --> 00:57:51.145
That you'll disappear without a trace?

00:57:54.445 --> 00:57:57.415
Come on, you know how I feel.

00:57:57.985 --> 00:58:00.425
You're not a bad guy, are you?

00:58:12.995 --> 00:58:14.735
So you are a bad guy.

00:58:28.615 --> 00:58:30.245
Then just kill me already.

00:58:32.715 --> 00:58:34.985
You're going to kill me anyway.

00:58:48.205 --> 00:58:51.175
Park Min Ho, the man you killed. His father resets this every time.

00:58:51.775 --> 00:58:52.905
Three minutes.

00:58:53.845 --> 00:58:57.575
All the time he had left to remember his son.

00:59:03.615 --> 00:59:06.155
Before this sand runs out, you'd better think hard.

00:59:07.225 --> 00:59:09.355
Is there even a single person in this world...

00:59:10.025 --> 00:59:11.525
who will genuinely remember you?

00:59:33.315 --> 00:59:34.315
Is there?

00:59:45.995 --> 00:59:47.425
Yes, there is!

00:59:48.665 --> 00:59:49.865
You!

00:59:51.995 --> 00:59:55.535
You'll have to be the one to remember me!

01:00:08.245 --> 01:00:09.745
(My moments of lucidity are getting shorter.)

01:00:09.815 --> 01:00:11.055
(And they last under 3 minutes.)

01:00:11.115 --> 01:00:12.885
(I'm leaving the things I must remember and never forget.)

01:00:15.055 --> 01:00:16.525
You!

01:00:18.295 --> 01:00:21.565
You'll have to be the one to remember me!

01:00:52.125 --> 01:00:53.255
Min Ho!

01:00:54.565 --> 01:00:55.995
Min Ho!

01:00:56.565 --> 01:00:59.795
Dad, hurry up. The sun's just starting to set.

01:01:03.035 --> 01:01:04.675
When I was coming up here,

01:01:05.105 --> 01:01:06.705
I didn't think you'd actually be here.

01:01:06.775 --> 01:01:09.475
Of course I'm here. We made a promise, Dad.

01:01:10.245 --> 01:01:11.375
We...

01:01:11.615 --> 01:01:13.475
promised to return here together, remember?

01:01:13.885 --> 01:01:16.745
- Yes. - The sky is beautiful today too.

01:01:16.785 --> 01:01:17.815
Right.

01:01:19.015 --> 01:01:21.155
I knew you'd find me, Dad.

01:01:24.355 --> 01:01:27.495
I'm sorry. It took me so long, didn't it?

01:01:27.695 --> 01:01:28.795
No, it's okay.

01:01:32.635 --> 01:01:33.665
Dad.

01:01:34.565 --> 01:01:36.835
You went through so much trying to find me.

01:01:38.235 --> 01:01:39.605
You really did.

01:01:44.215 --> 01:01:45.275
Dad.

01:01:46.175 --> 01:01:48.545
I'll go on ahead and wait for you,

01:01:49.445 --> 01:01:50.885
so you take your time...

01:01:51.515 --> 01:01:53.155
and come join me much later.

01:01:53.855 --> 01:01:54.885
Okay?

01:01:57.395 --> 01:01:58.855
And don't you worry about me.

01:01:59.555 --> 01:02:00.665
Min Ho.

01:02:04.735 --> 01:02:05.735
Thank you.

01:02:55.785 --> 01:02:58.784
(Dong Su, please give me a call. Seong Cheol)

01:02:58.785 --> 01:03:00.085
Dong Su.

01:03:00.625 --> 01:03:01.755
Please give me a call.

01:03:10.465 --> 01:03:11.465
Dong Su.

01:03:13.565 --> 01:03:17.105
I've been waiting for this phone to ring.

01:03:19.105 --> 01:03:21.645
Your son Min Ho is on his final journey.

01:03:22.905 --> 01:03:24.775
You have to be the one to see him off.

01:03:30.185 --> 01:03:31.784
(Deluxe Taxi)

01:03:31.785 --> 01:03:33.255
Thank you.

01:03:33.815 --> 01:03:35.555
Thank you so much.

01:03:46.735 --> 01:03:49.735
(The late Park Min Ho)

01:04:15.725 --> 01:04:18.035
(The late Park Min Ho)

01:04:25.035 --> 01:04:26.235
Min Ho.

01:04:27.645 --> 01:04:28.705
Yes?

01:04:29.005 --> 01:04:30.575
The sky is so beautiful.

01:04:31.915 --> 01:04:33.615
It's the kind of sky you love.

01:04:36.015 --> 01:04:37.045
Look at that.

01:04:38.955 --> 01:04:40.015
It is.

01:04:40.825 --> 01:04:42.425
It's really beautiful today too.

01:04:56.135 --> 01:04:58.135
(The late Park Min Ho)

01:06:56.325 --> 01:06:58.225
(Special thanks to our guest star, Um Mun Suk)

01:07:10.305 --> 01:07:13.335
(Taxi Driver 3)

01:07:13.705 --> 01:07:16.945
You know, my dream was to be an idol.

01:07:17.345 --> 01:07:21.185
I'm going all-in on you, risking everything I have.

01:07:21.245 --> 01:07:22.345
Where are we going?

01:07:22.585 --> 01:07:25.515
The next thing she knew, she woke up somewhere strange.

01:07:25.785 --> 01:07:28.355
Then what am I supposed to do?

01:07:28.855 --> 01:07:30.655
If you can't debut now, the group is done.

01:07:30.755 --> 01:07:32.625
I really don't know anything.

01:07:32.955 --> 01:07:35.495
Just remember how badly you wanted this.

01:07:35.695 --> 01:07:38.895
What if the agency is the one that's been threatening our client?

01:07:39.165 --> 01:07:40.335
You're in for a beating today.

01:07:41.005 --> 01:07:42.835
Looks like we'll need someone on the inside.

01:07:43.205 --> 01:07:44.475
We'll replace the manager.